722
01:01:59.833 --> 01:02:01.625
Where are the keys?

723
01:02:01.667 --> 01:02:03.917
Here, open this.

724
01:02:16.583 --> 01:02:19.208
Where are Terabithian warriors
when you need them?

725
01:02:19.292 --> 01:02:21.125
I don't know.

726
01:02:24.792 --> 01:02:26.875
Great. Now there's three of us.

727
01:02:33.750 --> 01:02:36.375
- Wow.
- Now we're even.

728
01:02:36.458 --> 01:02:37.875
Attack!

729
01:02:47.083 --> 01:02:51.292
Dead meat! Dead meat!
Dead meat! Dead meat! Dead meat!

730
01:02:52.833 --> 01:02:53.792
Come on.

731
01:02:54.500 --> 01:02:57.917
- Come on, P.T.
- Dead meat!

732
01:03:20.583 --> 01:03:23.125
Be careful!
You're almost there.

733
01:03:30.333 --> 01:03:32.667
Jess!

734
01:03:33.208 --> 01:03:34.458
Jess!

735
01:03:52.792 --> 01:03:53.917
Hey.

736
01:04:43.875 --> 01:04:45.958
- See ya!
- Yeah, see ya.

737
01:05:36.542 --> 01:05:39.042
Jess! I called you three times.

738
01:05:39.125 --> 01:05:40.333
It's your girlfriend.

739
01:05:40.417 --> 01:05:42.500
She's not my girlfriend.

740
01:05:43.583 --> 01:05:45.708
<i>- Hey.
- Hello, Jess.</i>

741
01:05:45.792 --> 01:05:47.792
Wait. Who is this?

742
01:05:47.875 --> 01:05:50.500
It's Saturday, but it's
your teacher, Ms. Edmunds.

743
01:05:50.583 --> 01:05:55.000
I was planning on taking my nephews
into the city to the museum,

744
01:05:55.042 --> 01:05:58.958
and my sister changed her plans
last minute, so I had a thought.

745
01:06:03.417 --> 01:06:06.208
- Hey, Mom.
- Hmm? Is it the baby?

746
01:06:06.292 --> 01:06:09.000
No, she's fine.
May Belle's got her.

747
01:06:09.083 --> 01:06:12.625
Teacher wants me to go
on a field trip today.

748
01:06:12.708 --> 01:06:15.500
- Is that OK?
- Mmm.

749
01:06:19.792 --> 01:06:21.708
Ms. Edmunds? Yeah, I can go.

750
01:06:29.917 --> 01:06:31.667
- All set?
- Yeah.

751
01:06:31.750 --> 01:06:33.167
- Yeah?
- Yes, ma'am.

752
01:06:40.417 --> 01:06:42.375
Forget something?

753
01:06:44.333 --> 01:06:46.667
No. I'm good.

754
01:07:22.833 --> 01:07:24.500
Wow.

755
01:07:29.875 --> 01:07:31.500
Honey, honey, stay here.

756
01:07:34.750 --> 01:07:37.333
- Do you like it?
- Yeah.

757
01:07:37.375 --> 01:07:40.500
It's Brueghel.
It's one of my favorites.

758
01:07:40.542 --> 01:07:43.917
I wonder if he started in notebooks
like you. I know da Vinci did.

759
01:07:48.708 --> 01:07:51.833
It's amazing how much
detail's put into it.

760
01:07:51.875 --> 01:07:54.208
You've been to a museum before, right?

761
01:07:54.292 --> 01:07:57.708
- No, it's my first time.
- Really?

762
01:07:57.792 --> 01:08:00.542
- Yup.
- Well, then I'm honored.

763
01:08:40.083 --> 01:08:41.875
It's such a nice day out.

764
01:08:41.958 --> 01:08:46.250
It's been raining so much, I began
to think it was like that Japanese myth

765
01:08:46.333 --> 01:08:50.333
where the sun goes into the cave
and vows never to come out.

766
01:08:50.417 --> 01:08:53.625
- You know about everything.
- Not by a long shot.

767
01:08:53.708 --> 01:08:55.708
But I do try to keep an open mind,

768
01:08:55.792 --> 01:08:58.375
and you'd be surprised
what finds its way in there.

769
01:08:58.458 --> 01:09:02.125
That's what Leslie Burke says.
She told me to keep my mind wide open.

770
01:09:02.208 --> 01:09:03.875
Leslie Burke is right.

771
01:09:03.917 --> 01:09:07.583
Mind like yours wide open,
you could create a whole new world.

772
01:09:15.458 --> 01:09:19.333
- Thank you very much.
- You're very welcome.

773
01:09:19.417 --> 01:09:23.042
- Maybe we could do this again sometime.
- Absolutely.

774
01:09:27.833 --> 01:09:30.292
- Hey, guys.
- See? I told you.

775
01:09:30.375 --> 01:09:32.417
Oh, my God, Jess!

776
01:09:34.083 --> 01:09:37.375
- Where in God's name have you been?
- Where have you been?

777
01:09:38.542 --> 01:09:40.875
Mom...

778
01:09:40.917 --> 01:09:43.417
I asked you. It wasn't like I...

779
01:09:43.500 --> 01:09:46.208
- They thought you were dead.
- Brenda, hush.

780
01:09:46.250 --> 01:09:48.042
Dead?

781
01:09:49.250 --> 01:09:51.042
What's going on?

782
01:09:57.792 --> 01:10:00.208
Your friend Leslie's dead.

783
01:10:02.042 --> 01:10:03.875
She drowned in a creek this morning.

784
01:10:03.917 --> 01:10:07.542
Apparently she tried to swing
across on a rope and it broke.

785
01:10:07.625 --> 01:10:09.875
They think she hit her head.

786
01:10:11.708 --> 01:10:15.167
No... No, it's not that kind of rope.

787
01:10:15.250 --> 01:10:18.875
It couldn't break.
It... wouldn't have.

788
01:10:18.917 --> 01:10:20.958
But it did.

789
01:10:24.250 --> 01:10:27.875
- I'm sorry, son.
- No, you're lying.

790
01:10:28.750 --> 01:10:32.792
- She's not even dead. You're lying!
- Jess!

791
01:12:07.000 --> 01:12:10.250
Hi, honey. You want some breakfast?

792
01:12:10.333 --> 01:12:13.083
I... I gotta do my chores first.

793
01:12:13.167 --> 01:12:15.917
Your dad's doing everything today.
You just sit down.

794
01:12:31.958 --> 01:12:33.708
Jess, your father and I thought

795
01:12:33.792 --> 01:12:36.417
we'd go to the Burkes today
and pay our respects.

796
01:12:36.500 --> 01:12:38.833
Just the three of us.

797
01:12:39.875 --> 01:12:41.292
Paying what?

798
01:13:02.750 --> 01:13:04.500
Prince Terrien. Shh.

799
01:13:05.417 --> 01:13:07.333
You must be Jess.

800
01:13:16.542 --> 01:13:21.250
I'm Mr. Aarons. This is my wife, Mary.
Very sorry about your loss.

801
01:13:21.333 --> 01:13:23.875
- I'm so sorry.
- Hi, Jess.

802
01:13:31.875 --> 01:13:33.875
She loved you, you know.

803
01:13:34.875 --> 01:13:36.375
You know, Leslie,

804
01:13:36.458 --> 01:13:40.375
she never had much luck
making friends at her old school.

805
01:13:40.458 --> 01:13:43.792
We were hoping that when
we moved out here she would...

806
01:13:48.042 --> 01:13:50.458
She said
if it wasn't for you...

807
01:13:52.875 --> 01:13:55.125
You're the best friend she's ever had.

808
01:13:55.208 --> 01:13:57.167
I wanna thank you for that.

809
01:13:58.667 --> 01:14:00.750
You're welcome.

810
01:14:03.833 --> 01:14:06.833
My wife and I were wondering
about the service.

811
01:14:10.375 --> 01:14:13.958
We've decided to bring Leslie
back home until the service.

812
01:14:19.708 --> 01:14:23.708
- Jess.
- Next time,

813
01:14:23.792 --> 01:14:26.750
we should invite Leslie to go.

814
01:14:28.625 --> 01:14:30.833
She'd like that.

815
01:14:40.292 --> 01:14:41.833
Hey, kid.

816
01:14:43.292 --> 01:14:45.417
Sorry about your friend.

817
01:14:47.917 --> 01:14:52.417
The purpose
of object pronouns...

818
01:14:52.500 --> 01:14:55.625
So looks like you're
the fastest kid in the class now, huh?

819
01:14:58.000 --> 01:15:00.083
It's a joke, dude.

820
01:15:04.667 --> 01:15:06.708
- Are you nuts?
- Jess Aarons.

821
01:15:07.292 --> 01:15:09.417
Go wait for me out in the hall.

822
01:15:10.833 --> 01:15:13.292
Silent reading until I get back.

823
01:15:22.625 --> 01:15:24.375
Jess...

824
01:15:31.042 --> 01:15:33.958
When my husband died...

825
01:15:34.000 --> 01:15:37.000
...people kept telling me not to cry.

826
01:15:38.125 --> 01:15:40.500
People kept trying to help me to forget.

827
01:15:43.792 --> 01:15:46.125
But I didn't wanna forget.

828
01:15:46.208 --> 01:15:48.542
Excuse me.

829
01:15:51.292 --> 01:15:53.917
The things that girl came up with.

830
01:15:55.958 --> 01:15:58.542
I don't get students like her too often.

831
01:16:03.125 --> 01:16:05.583
So I realize...

832
01:16:05.625 --> 01:16:08.375
...that if it's hard for me...

833
01:16:08.458 --> 01:16:10.958
...how much harder it must be for you.

834
01:16:58.542 --> 01:17:00.708
Hurry up.
We're gonna miss the bus!

835
01:17:10.083 --> 01:17:11.833
Hey.

836
01:17:59.000 --> 01:18:01.042
Leslie?!

837
01:18:25.750 --> 01:18:27.875
Jess!

838
01:18:27.958 --> 01:18:29.458
Leslie!

839
01:18:29.542 --> 01:18:33.000
- Jess!
- Leslie!

840
01:18:39.458 --> 01:18:41.083
Lesl...

841
01:18:41.167 --> 01:18:44.125
Help me, I can't get across! Hurry!

842
01:18:45.333 --> 01:18:47.333
May Belle?

843
01:18:49.750 --> 01:18:51.958
Hold on! Don't move!

844
01:18:53.583 --> 01:18:56.083
Here, grab my arm.
I got you, don't worry.

845
01:19:01.417 --> 01:19:03.958
- What were you thinking?
- I was worried about you!

846
01:19:04.042 --> 01:19:06.833
Well, don't be. I don't want you here!

847
01:19:07.458 --> 01:19:10.250
- But I wanna come with you.
- This is our place. Go home.

848
01:19:10.333 --> 01:19:12.167
This is our place!

849
01:19:16.333 --> 01:19:17.667
I said go home!

850
01:19:32.792 --> 01:19:34.667
Honey, what's the matter?

851
01:19:35.625 --> 01:19:37.583
What's the matter?

852
01:19:37.667 --> 01:19:39.583
What's the matter, baby?

853
01:20:44.208 --> 01:20:45.917
No!

854
01:20:47.500 --> 01:20:49.208
Jess!

855
01:20:50.208 --> 01:20:53.000
It's OK, Jess.
It's OK, son, it's OK.

856
01:20:53.042 --> 01:20:54.833
It's all gone.

857
01:20:58.333 --> 01:21:00.792
Is it like the Bible says?

858
01:21:00.875 --> 01:21:02.750
Is she going to hell?

859
01:21:03.458 --> 01:21:05.250
I don't know everything about God,

860
01:21:05.333 --> 01:21:08.208
but I do know He's not
gonna send that little girl to hell.

861
01:21:08.250 --> 01:21:11.625
Then I'm going to hell
because it's all my fault.

862
01:21:11.708 --> 01:21:15.375
Don't you think that even for a minute.

863
01:21:15.458 --> 01:21:18.083
But it is.

864
01:21:18.167 --> 01:21:22.375
I didn't invite her
to go to the museum with me.

865
01:21:22.458 --> 01:21:25.792
I didn't wanna invite her.

866
01:21:25.875 --> 01:21:29.167
I wasn't there to go with her.

867
01:21:29.208 --> 01:21:32.333
- It's my fault.
- No, no, no, no.

868
01:21:32.417 --> 01:21:34.583
It's not your fault.

869
01:21:34.667 --> 01:21:37.292
None of that makes it so.

870
01:21:37.375 --> 01:21:39.542
It's a terrible thing.

871
01:21:39.625 --> 01:21:44.250
It doesn't make any sense,
but it's not your fault, Jess.

872
01:21:49.292 --> 01:21:52.958
She brought you something special
when she came here, didn't she?

873
01:21:56.125 --> 01:21:58.542
That's what you hold on to.

874
01:22:01.583 --> 01:22:04.083
That's how you keep her alive.

875
01:22:24.333 --> 01:22:25.667
May Belle?

876
01:22:34.375 --> 01:22:35.750
Look.

877
01:22:37.542 --> 01:22:39.417
I'm sorry I pushed you.

878
01:22:41.625 --> 01:22:44.875
That was stupid and wrong...

879
01:22:47.000 --> 01:22:49.083
...and I really miss you talking to me.

880
01:23:29.458 --> 01:23:31.875
She's in your hands now.

881
01:23:55.125 --> 01:23:56.250
Hey!

882
01:23:58.083 --> 01:23:59.375
Wait!

883
01:24:01.417 --> 01:24:02.458
Wait!

884
01:24:04.750 --> 01:24:06.167
Hey!

885
01:24:12.083 --> 01:24:15.167
Jess? I'm sorry.
I didn't... I didn't see you.

886
01:24:15.250 --> 01:24:19.000
Can I use the lumber by your house?

887
01:24:19.083 --> 01:24:20.750
Yeah, yeah. Of course.

888
01:24:20.833 --> 01:24:23.542
Anything you see, you just...

889
01:24:24.417 --> 01:24:27.792
You know, I meant to...
I meant to give you Prince Terrien,

890
01:24:27.875 --> 01:24:31.083
but I... can't seem to give him up.

891
01:24:32.917 --> 01:24:35.000
Leslie would've wanted you to have him.

892
01:24:35.083 --> 01:24:36.625
Yeah.

893
01:26:00.042 --> 01:26:03.417
We're playing. By ourselves.

894
01:26:04.917 --> 01:26:08.875
OK, but I know the most
incredible place to play.

895
01:26:08.958 --> 01:26:12.042
You gotta promise you're
not gonna tell anybody about it.

896
01:26:12.083 --> 01:26:16.208
Not Brenda, not Ellie, not even Joycie.

897
01:26:16.292 --> 01:26:19.875
Tell Joycie a secret between you and me?

898
01:26:19.958 --> 01:26:21.500
She's nothing but a baby.

899
01:26:21.583 --> 01:26:24.833
You're right, and she's not ready
to be a princess yet.

900
01:26:24.917 --> 01:26:26.750
You have to train her and stuff.

901
01:26:26.833 --> 01:26:29.875
Princess? Who gets to be the princess?

902
01:26:39.625 --> 01:26:41.375
Step down.

903
01:26:44.833 --> 01:26:46.250
Watch your step.

904
01:26:53.750 --> 01:26:55.583
You're not peeking, are you?

905
01:26:57.667 --> 01:27:00.458
Step up. There you go.

906
01:27:07.875 --> 01:27:09.667
All right.

907
01:27:16.083 --> 01:27:18.083
OK. Open them.

908
01:27:23.833 --> 01:27:27.875
Wow. Did you make this?

909
01:27:29.333 --> 01:27:31.042
Yep.

910
01:27:33.875 --> 01:27:35.667
Hold on a second.

911
01:27:44.333 --> 01:27:47.708
Look! They must've heard the rumor,

912
01:27:47.792 --> 01:27:52.542
that the beautiful girl arriving today
is the new future ruler of Terabithia.

913
01:27:52.625 --> 01:27:55.917
- Who heard?
- The Terabithians.

914
01:27:56.000 --> 01:27:58.250
They've been waiting.

915
01:27:58.333 --> 01:28:00.333
Where?

916
01:28:00.417 --> 01:28:03.875
- I don't see them.
- It's an ancient forest, May Belle,

917
01:28:03.958 --> 01:28:06.333
full of magical creatures
and friendly giants,

918
01:28:06.417 --> 01:28:08.708
anything you can imagine.

919
01:28:08.792 --> 01:28:10.750
But you gotta look really hard.

920
01:28:10.792 --> 01:28:13.708
But keep your mind wide open.

921
01:28:22.333 --> 01:28:24.167
So, what do you think?

922
01:28:28.583 --> 01:28:31.000
Can there be purple flowers?

923
01:28:33.125 --> 01:28:35.542
Anything you want.

924
01:28:36.500 --> 01:28:38.500
Wow.

925
01:28:39.917 --> 01:28:41.208
And a castle.

926
01:28:41.292 --> 01:28:44.083
A big one, with towers and flags.

927
01:28:44.125 --> 01:28:46.458
Of course.

928
01:28:49.292 --> 01:28:52.125
Look, Jess. It's beautiful.

929
01:28:56.000 --> 01:28:57.708
Is there a king?

930
01:28:57.792 --> 01:28:59.208
Are you the king, Jess?

931
01:28:59.292 --> 01:29:01.875
Only if you're princess.

932
01:29:47.417 --> 01:29:49.792
Terabithia.

